Law and Order: Episode 5

None of these actions make our country safer or citizens more prosperous, but here are some of the things the new Administration delivered this week:

-Firing the staff at the National Nuclear Security Administration responsible for managing America's nuclear weapons;
-Firing the USDA team responsible for stopping the spread of avian flu;
-Firing 6,700 IRS agents whose primary responsibility was chasing down rich tax cheats;
-Freezing the hiring and onboarding of thousands of federal firefighters;
-Confirming Kash Patel — who is dangerous, dishonest, and unqualified, to say the least — to lead the FBI after he promised to get revenge on the President's "enemies";
-Weaponizing the Department of Justice, as promised, to seek revenge against critics; in this case, opening a DOJ investigation against Congressman Robert Garcia for comments he made that were critical of Elon Musk;
-The ongoing silence from Republicans who know what the Administration is doing is wrong but won't say it.

Not exactly making America great again.

To be continued.
